definitions.definition: A state in the Deep South and South Central regions of the United States . Capital: Baton Rouge . Largest city: New Orleans .
A vast territory in central North America :

subdefinitions.definition: An administrative district of New France . (1682–1769; 1801–1803)
A former territory of the United States . (1805–1812)

definitions.definition: A city in Pike County , Missouri , named for the founder's daughter, Louisiana Bayse.
A ghost town in Douglas County , Kansas .
The University of Louisiana at Lafayette , and especially its athletic program, the Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns .
